begin_memory_text: At the beginning of the conversation, we mostly did introductions. We talked about where we're from and where our families are. We talked about where we went/go to school, and we talked about how his kids are doing in school.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation, we talked more about the coronavirus, and how it has affected our lives. I told him about school and how we have to test twice a week. He talked about how his kids are mostly locked indoors and have been doing online school for 8 months.
end_memory_text: At the end of the conversation, we talked about the situation of our current lives. We talked about how we're dealing with our individual situations, and our feelings towards all the current events.
rest_of_day_open: I'm currently in school, so the rest of the week will be pretty much like the last few weeks. I will be doing classes online, while practicing my instrument a few hours a day. I have recently moved into an apartment with my roommate, so I will be cooking and enjoying life with my roommate.
critical_positive: I think we were both very engaged in the conversation. We both did a pretty good job of letting the conversation flow, whether it be current events or his children, we talked about whatever came to mind and we weren't shy about any details. It was nice to talk to someone anonymous and open up about some details in my life!
critical_negative: I don't think there were too many things that didn't work well. It is always a little awkward at the beginning of meeting someone you've never seen before, but this was almost as good as it's ever gotten for me. He was nice, and we were able to chat about many things.

begin_memory_text: We began by talking about our backgrounds. I went first, and then he mentioned that he was a college student in Boston. I also attended school in Boston, and we connected over that. Then we talked about the current status of Covid in each area.
middle_memory_text: My counterpart is a music student, and we talked about his training. He currently has a minor injury, and it was interesting to talk about the his plan to fix as well as to progress in his career.
end_memory_text: We talked about the hours of training that he was able to go through, and I compared it to my son's baseball training. The chance to be the best in your field is remote, but the value of work and training can be brought from one area to the next.
rest_of_day_open: Well it is the weekend, and my wife took my kids to a beach house. So I am bachelor. I am going to spend the weekend building shelves for my shed and organizing the space. I plan on taking myself out to a restaurant to have a beer or two and a nice steak. Then I will probably watch a movie or a baseball playoff game.
critical_positive: We each talked about our life experiences - starting with general broad terms, and when we found some common overlap, we were able to go deeper on those topics. Because my partner was younger than I was, I was able to compare his experiences more with my hopes for my younger kids. But the commonalities, I feel, helped us relax and feel more comfortable.
critical_negative: It took a little while to find common ground, but we were able to hit our stride 5 or 10 minutes into the conversation and really I felt like it was  good conversation throughout the entire chat. I imagine he had some reticence seeing someone much older, and he must have wondered because of my appearance that it would probably be tough to find commonality
